<para>
  The <classname>MeshMaterialDisplay</classname> fills each &mesh;
  element with the color of the &material; assigned to it.  If the
  element has no <classname>Material</classname>, or the
  <classname>Material</classname> has no <xref
  linkend="Property-Color"/> <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Property">property</link>,
  then the element is not filled.
</para>
<para>
  <classname>MeshMaterialDisplay</classname> differs from the <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonMaterialDisplay"><classname>SkeletonMaterialDisplay</classname></link>
  in that Mesh elements may be drawn at their <link
  linkend="Output-Position-original">original</link>, undisplaced
  positions, at their <link
  linkend="Output-Position-actual">actual</link> displaced positions
  (computed from the <varname>Displacement</varname> field), or at
  <link linkend="Output-Position-enhanced">enhanced</link> positions
  (using a scaled <varname>Displacement</varname> field).
</para>

